Here’s a structured Reviewer Feedback Template you can add to your PRs in crystalcastle. It gives collaborators a clear, standardized way to leave comments — whether approving, requesting changes, or suggesting improvements.  

---

📋 Reviewer Feedback Template

- Approval  
  - ✅ Code changes meet requirements.  
  - ✅ CI/CD pipeline passes without errors.  
  - ✅ Documentation is clear and aligned.  
  - Comment: “Looks good to me — approved.”  

- Request Changes  
  - ❌ Issues found in schema validation or pipeline.  
  - ❌ Dashboard logic breaks existing components.  
  - ❌ Documentation missing or unclear.  
  - Comment: “Please fix [specific issue] before approval.”  

- Suggestions  
  - 💡 Possible optimizations in code readability.  
  - 💡 UI/UX improvements for dashboard layout.  
  - 💡 Additional notes for README clarity.  
  - Comment: “Consider [suggestion] to improve maintainability.”  

---

✅ Why this helps
- Keeps reviewer comments consistent and actionable.  
- Separates blocking issues (request changes) from non‑blocking suggestions.  
- Makes approvals faster by giving reviewers a clear structure.  

